In his weekly address, President Trump spoke from the deck of the new aircraft carrier, the Gerald R. Ford. He emphasized the importance of American military might and the need to provide the military with the resources it needs. He discussed the reduction in manpower and the aging equipment in the Army, Air Force, and Navy. He expressed his commitment to investing in the military as a means to achieve peace and support the men and women in uniform. He also touched upon his vision for national rebuilding, including the elimination of the defense sequester. He concluded by urging Americans to work together to seize the opportunity for national renewal.